# 1. Project Overview

This project implements the final firmware for an automated grow-bench irrigation system using an ESP32 microcontroller. The system continuously monitors soil moisture and automatically controls irrigation through a solenoid valve using relay switching.

The firmware supports both automatic irrigation and manual override modes. Additional features include telemetry upload to the Zelbytes IoT Lab cloud API, serial monitoring commands, and a local web server for remote control.

Main goals of the project:

* Monitor soil moisture in real time
* Automatically irrigate when soil becomes dry
* Allow manual override using button or commands
* Upload telemetry to cloud server
* Provide remote control via browser

